     <h3>
      Congratulations! When you receive your degree from the UCR School of Business Administration and the A. Gary Anderson Graduate School of Management, you automatically become a member of the SoBA Alumni Network.
     </h3>
     <p>
      Please join our
      <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/UCR-School-of-Business-Administration-Alumni-Network/101342929912907" target="_blank">
       Facebook
      </a>
      and
      <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/groups/UC-Riverside-School-Business-Administration-3074570?mostPopular=&amp;gid=3074570" target="_blank">
       LinkedIn
      </a>
      groups now to stay in touch. You are following in the footsteps of many leading thinkers before you who have benefited from a quality UC business education.
     </p>
     <p>
      As a member of the SoBA Alumni Network you will enjoy many opportunities including the following:
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       An invitation to join us at our annual
       <a href="http://soba.ucr.edu/involved/homecoming.html" target="_blank">
        Homecoming
       </a>
       festivities. Itâ€™s a free event for our alumni &amp; friends of the business school.
      </li>
      <li>
       Invitations to regional alumni receptions. These mixers are a great opportunity for you to stay connected with the business school and your former classmates.
      </li>
      <li>
       Opportunities to network for jobs. Make use of the SoBA alumni network, through
       <a href="http://www.linkedin.com/groups/UC-Riverside-School-Business-Administration-3074570?mostPopular=&amp;gid=3074570" target="_blank">
        LinkedIn
       </a>
       , and connect with potential employers with UCR business school roots!
      </li>
      <li>
       Quarterly
       <a href="http://soba.ucr.edu/involved/newsletter/" target="_blank">
        alumni &amp; friends e-newsletters
       </a>
       that will keep you abreast of the latest news from SoBA and your fellow alumni.
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
      <strong>
       Participate in the SoBA Alumni Network and reap the benefits of being a graduate of the UCR School of Business Administration, home of the A. Gary Anderson Graduate School of Management.
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p class="section2" style="padding-left: 30px;">
      <span style="color: #23408e; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 15px;">
       <em>
        Recruit Current Business School Students
       </em>
      </span>
     </p>
     <img alt="Seals" class="img_R_borderless" height="" src="http://soba.ucr.edu/images/seals.png" width=""/>
     <p style="padding-left: 30px;">
      Are you an employer who would like to post job opportunities for SoBA's current students?
     </p>
     <ul style="padding-left: 30px;">
      <li>
       <span style="line-height: 18px; font-size: 12px;">
        To post opportunities for current undergraduate students, contact the
        <a href="http://careers.ucr.edu/" target="_blank">
         UCR Career Center
        </a>
        .
       </span>
      </li>
      <li>
       <span style="font-size: 13px;">
        To post opportunities for current MBA students, visit
        <a href="http://agsm.ucr.edu/mba/careers.html" target="_blank">
         MBA Career Services
        </a>
        .
       </span>
      </li>
     </ul>
